The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Film-maker Rituparno Ghosh was discharged on Thursday afternoon from the south Calcutta nursing home where he was admitted on April 30.  Rituparnos diabetes, early pancreatitis and blood sugar are all under control. An endocrinologist and a gastroenterologist have seen him, said consultant physician Rajib Seal, who supervised the treatment. Ghosh has been advised bed-rest for about 10 days.  Cellphone theft: Seventy-six cellphones were found on a 15-year-old boy during a raid in a bar near New Town on Wednesday night. Police said the boy and three of his friends, who are now absconding, stole the handsets from employees of a cellphone distributor in Baguiati on Tuesday.																																																								  Airport arrest: A 24-year-old man was arrested at the airport on Thursday after he was sent back from China for using a forged visa. Vikramjit Singh, a resident of Jalandhar, went to Kunming from Calcutta on May 2.																																																								  Bail plea: A high court division bench on Thursday rejected an anticipatory bail plea by Shyamal Kumar Das, alias Hubaa Shyamal, an Independent candidate in the upcoming Konnagar Municipality elections. Das was apprehending arrest in connection with an extortion case.																																																								  Lightning death: Rubina Sarkar, a 19-year-old homemaker, died after being struck by lightning at Rajdanga in Kasba on Thursday evening.																																																								  Run over: A 50-year-old man was run over by a Tata Sumo that had jumped signal at Bangur Avenue early on Thursday. Debnarayan Gupta, an Agartala-based trader, was on his way to Bangur Avenue after seeing off his son at the airport. Debnarayan was taken to a nursing home where he was declared dead.																																																								  Fatal mishap: Munshi Farid Ahmed, a 37-year-old motorcyclist, died after being hit by a truck at Paglahat near Calcutta Leather Complex on Thursday. He was taken to hospital, where doctors declared him dead. The driver fled but the truck was impounded.                                                                                                                                               
